libsqon
------------------------------------------
The purpose of SQON is simple: to make interaction with SQL databases as easy
as any JSON API. So many languages interact flawlessly with JSON for data
transfer as well as (clearly) object notation.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libjansson4-2.13.1-1
  libmariadb3-3.0.9-1
  libpq5-17.4-1
  libsqon-devel-1.2.0a-1bl1
  libsqon1-1.2.0a-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libjansson-devel-2.13.1-1
  libmariadb-devel-3.0.9-1
  libpq-devel-17.4-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/delwink/libsqon

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/delwink/libsqon/archive/refs/tags/1.2.0a.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsqon-1.2.0a-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsqon-1.2.0a-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsqon-1.2.0a-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsqon-1.2.0a-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsqon1-1.2.0a-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsqon-devel-1.2.0a-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libsqon)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libsqon.README
  /usr/share/doc/libsqon/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libsqon/README
  /usr/share/doc/libsqon/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/libsqon/basic-tutorial.md

(libsqon1)
  /usr/bin/cygsqon-1.dll

(libsqon-devel)
  /usr/include/sqon.h
  /usr/lib/libsqon.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/sqon.pc

